Class LobbyEvent

java.lang.Object
org.example.galaxy_trucker.ClientServer.Messages.LobbyEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Event
public class LobbyEvent extends Object implements Event
Represents an event that occurs in a game lobby. This class contains information about the game lobby such as its ID, level, maximum number of players, and the list of players currently in the lobby. It is used to transmit lobby-related events between different parts of the system.

    • LobbyEvent

      public LobbyEvent()
      Constructs a new instance of the LobbyEvent class. This no-argument constructor initializes a LobbyEvent instance with default values. It is primarily used for deserialization or for creating an empty event object to be populated later. The LobbyEvent represents an event occurring in a game lobby, facilitating communication related to the lobby in the system.

    • LobbyEvent

      public LobbyEvent(String gameId, int lv, ArrayList<String> players, int maxPlayers)
      Constructs a new LobbyEvent instance with the specified game ID, level, list of players, and the maximum number of players.
      Parameters:
      gameId - the unique identifier of the game session
      lv - the level of the game or lobby
      players - the list of player names currently in the lobby
      maxPlayers - the maximum number of players allowed in the lobby
